label: Full Name
definition: Preferred form of personal name for display as a string.

label: Reference Details
definition: Detailed information related to a class.
usage: Detailed information about the resource being referenced.
examples: `This dataset includes a Darwin Core Archive of the ~8000 specimens digitised to date, of which ~80% also have an associated label image.`

label: Reference Text
definition: A generic text property to describe a class.
usage: A short title for the reference.
examples: `Digitised specimen records on the NHM Data Portal`, `BGBM loans policy`, `Herbarium Wikipedia page`, `NMNH website`, `Related sequences in GenBank`

label: Resource URI
definition: A preferably resolvable URI to uniquely identify a concept.
usage: A preferably resolvable URI providing access to the resource defined in the reference.
